verbose_text: Also He and co-workers reported CO 2 activation by Cu 2 H 2 -, with strong evidence for the formation of a C-H bond, leading to Cu 2 (HCO 2) H -.18 As all decarboxylation reactions observed here are endothermic, the reverse reactions with copper centers leading to formate seem to be a general feature in the activation of CO 2 by copper (I) hydrides.
